# Slide Content Filtering for AI Summary & Quiz

The AI currently processes **every** PDF slide including title slides, professor contact info, exam date announcements, and other non-educational metadata. This results in useless summaries and quiz questions about instructor emails and lecture dates.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend AI Service

#### [MODIFY] [ai_service.py](file:///c:/Users/Osama/ascend-academy/backend/services/ai_service.py)

Add a new `is_metadata_slide(text) â†’ bool` function that detects non-educational slides using a **two-layer** approach:

**Layer 1 â€” Heuristic keyword detection** (fast, no API call):
- Count matches against metadata-indicator patterns: email addresses, dates (`DD.MM.YYYY`, `MM/DD/YYYY`), keywords like `instructor`, `professor`, `contact`, `office hours`, `exam date`, `lecture \d+`, `fachbereich`, `universitĂ¤t`, `department`, etc.
- Check if the slide text is **too short** (< 50 meaningful characters after stripping whitespace) â€” likely a title-only slide.
- If the ratio of metadata keywords to total words is high (> 50%), classify as metadata.

**Layer 2 â€” Structural analysis:**
- If a slide is the **first or second page** of the PDF, and it matches common title-slide patterns (course name + lecture number + instructor), classify as metadata.
- Slides consisting **only** of a heading + a list of names/emails/dates get classified as metadata.

Also update [generate_summary](file:///c:/Users/Osama/ascend-academy/backend/services/ai_service.py#92-116) and [generate_quiz](file:///c:/Users/Osama/ascend-academy/backend/services/ai_service.py#118-168) prompts to include an explicit instruction: *"Ignore any administrative metadata such as instructor names, contact info, dates, or logistics."*

